In this statement, the President emphasizes the importance of trade enforcement in U.S. trade policy. He highlights the efforts made to protect American workers and improve labor laws with trading partners worldwide. The President supports new tools that would level the playing field for U.S. workers, businesses, and farmers. He expresses his satisfaction with the Trade Facilitation and Trade Enforcement Act and urges swift consideration by the relevant committees. The President also mentions several tools, such as Super 301 and elements of the ENFORCE Act, that would strengthen trade facilitation and enforcement of the rules. He calls for the repeal of the consumptive demand exception for child and forced labor. The President expresses his willingness to work with both chambers to improve provisions and ensure effective enforcement. He emphasizes that these enforcement tools complement new trade agreements and urges swift passage of this legislation.